-- Infrastructure Development Finance Raises 4.15 Billion Rupees Selling Debt
-- B y   S u p r o t i p   G h o s h
-- 2010-09-29T07:22:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/infrastructure-development-finance-raises-4-15-billion-rupees-selling-debt.html
Infrastructure Development Finance
Co. , an Indian state-run lender to power and road projects, sold
4.15 billion rupees ($92 million) of 10- and 15-year bonds,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The Chennai-based issuer raised 1.55 billion rupees from
10-year bonds that pay a coupon of 8.72 percent, and 2.6 billion
rupees from 15-year, 8.82 percent notes, the data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Suprotip Ghosh in Mumbai 
